results.lead_paragraph: The astronauts aboard the space shuttle Discovery pitched an ultraviolet telescope into orbit today after a delay caused by yet another communication problem. It was the crew's second satellite release in two days and another major objective of the 10-day shuttle mission.

headline.main: Astronauts Get Ready To Land In the Dark

results.snippet: The astronauts aboard the Discovery packed up today for the shuttle's first landing in Florida darkness after a mission that paved the way for the repair of the Hubble Space Telescope and encounters with Russia's Mir space station.   They tried out...
results.lead_paragraph: The astronauts aboard the Discovery packed up today for the shuttle's first landing in Florida darkness after a mission that paved the way for the repair of the Hubble Space Telescope and encounters with Russia's Mir space station. They tried out space-walking tools and flight positions for the Hubble mission in December, which is considered the most ambitious shuttle mission ever. They also tested navigation aids for an encounter with Mir next year and a docking with Mir the year after that.

headline.main: Government Dream Car; Washington and Detroit Pool Resources To Devise a New Approach to Technology

results.snippet: As the White House and Detroit set a goal today of developing a reliable, well-priced car that is three times as energy efficient as those now on the road, they did far more than lay out a research target. They are drafting a new model for how...
results.lead_paragraph: As the White House and Detroit set a goal today of developing a reliable, well-priced car that is three times as energy efficient as those now on the road, they did far more than lay out a research target. They are drafting a new model for how Washington and industry interact. Like the quest for the car, it is a step down an unknown road. This is not a stab at building a better mousetrap; it is a new approach to mice.
